node.text:
One More Cup of Coffee…

We made it out here for sunrise and coffee and stayed a little longer than usual- enjoying the “calm before the storm.”

I’m sharing the glow of this beautiful summer morning with you, awed by the tranquility of it, knowing just how quickly it will change. (swipe!)

We spent the rest of the day battening down the hatches, clearing the decks and cleaning up the property as Hurricane Henri makes his path directly toward us.

It’s been 30 years since we were hit by a hurricane. Compounded by the full moon Sunday night (an unusual Blue Moon) which will cause an astronomical high tide, we are sure to experience severe flooding. 

We are lucky to be perched almost 40’ above the sea, but my neighbors and friends in low lying areas are at greater risk. And, we have A LOT of windows😬.

This is no joke if you are in Henri’s path- Be careful-Hopefully the storm will head to the east, remain a tropical storm and all of this is for nothing! 
Stay safe everyone!!
🌀
#welivehere

node.text:
A Little Gift…

I always love getting this room ready for Oma to visit. I took these pics on the day she arrived a few weeks ago.

Today she left for Tante Stef’s (just a few miles away) where she will spend the next few weeks.

But, not without leaving me a little something homemade … swipe through to see what she left on the pillow!🤭🥰

node.text:
Living with Neutrals…

It’s always so hard to add color in our living room. The backdrop of windows do the work of bringing color in and the natural light and colors change dramatically throughout the day.

It’s a challenge to choose quiet pieces that bring just the right amount of personality to these front rooms!

I absolutely love the hand-knotted Carmel Rug from @serenaandlily that I added in here this summer, the bold pattern adds a layer of interest while the subtle tone keeps everything soothing!
It’s luxurious but still casual-both in the evening and during the day! 
(SWIPE!)

I’ve paired it with their Ridge Stripe pillow, a soft yarn-dyed cotton with beautiful stripe details and tassels, to finish off my favorite little corner!
#welivehere

This was sometime last week after a perfectly overcast, cold and dreary summer day.

Sunset, in Progression…

There was no sign of a sunset last night with the cloud cover. 
But our unpredictable skies cleared and at the last minute this one crept up on us-the best of the summer so far!

I snapped a few pics along the way, swipe!

(I’m off to the Vineyard for dinner, I’ll try and share in stories!)
#welivehere

node.text:
When It Rains…

The upside is I don’t have to do any watering! My front pots are happy!

I replanted my baskets over the weekend- @mahoneysgarden had so many beautiful flowers- it was hard to choose! August is my month for color- this year I used purples and deep pink!
(I added some cut hydrangeas til the baskets fill in.)

I have an interior plastic pot and saucer inside the baskets and I use an upside down bucket to prop them up to the right height.
#welivehere

Sunshine…

For three days in a row, so we opened all the doors and windows and let summer (and a few bees!) in.

Can you believe we had 26 days of rain in July? I call that a wash!
